=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09PepsiCo agreed to acquire Quaker Oats, an American food and dri=
nk company,=20
for shares worth $13.4 billion. Quaker had turned down an offer from PepsiC=
o;=20
a bid from Coca-Cola was halted by Coke=01,s own board. PepsiCo gets Quaker=
=01,s=20
Gatorade brand, which has an 84.1% share of the =01&sports=018 drink market=
 in=20
America.
=09=09=09=09See article: Pepsi bags QuakerE+
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Corus, forged from the merger of British Steel and Hoogovens, a=
 Dutch rival,=20
abandoned its experiment of employing two chief executives. Both are to=20
leave. The unwieldy compromise, needed to facilitate the merger, slowed dow=
n=20
decision-making at a time of declining demand for steel, which had led to=
=20
losses and a declining share price.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Pernod Ricard and Diageo announced that they had agreed to bid =
jointly for=20
the drinks business of Seagram, which is to be auctioned for a sum likely t=
o=20
exceed $7 billion after Seagram completes its merger with Vivendi, a French=
=20
conglomerate. A side-deal by the suppliers of Captain Morgan, Seagram=01,s=
=20
premium rum, with Allied Domecq, rivals for the rest of Seagram, has not=20
deterred Pernod and Diageo. Bacardi, in alliance with Brown-Forman, an=20
American firm, is also interested.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Bad banks
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Bank of America issued a profit warning for the fourth quarter,=
 blaming=20
rising bad debts and poor investment-banking results. Its shares hit a=20
12-month low.=20
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Deutsche Bank announced that it would reorganise its five main =
units into=20
only two, covering investment banking and asset management, and retail=20
operations. The bank hopes to take advantage of cross-selling opportunities=
=20
in both units.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09ING Barings, an Anglo-Dutch investment bank with a doubtful fut=
ure, lost its=20
chairman and his deputy. The departures may foreshadow a greater exodus.=20
